    <div class="container">
        <h2>Personal Safety Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Avoid walking alone at night.</li>
            <li>Stay in well-lit areas.</li>
            <li>Keep your phone charged and easily accessible.</li>
            <li>Trust your instincts; if something doesn't feel right, leave the situation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Online Safety Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords for online accounts.</li>
            <li>Avoid sharing personal information on social media.</li>
            <li>Be cautious when sharing personal information with strangers online.</li>
            <li>Regularly update your privacy settings on social media platforms.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Home Safety Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Lock doors and windows when at home.</li>
            <li>Install a peephole in your front door.</li>
            <li>Do not open the door to strangers.</li>
            <li>Have emergency contacts on speed dial.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>General Safety Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Listen to your gut feelings. If something feels off, take it seriously and act accordingly.</li>
            <li> Be mindful of your environment, especially in unfamiliar or potentially risky places.
            </li>
            <li>Share your plans with a trusted friend or family member. Let them know where you're going and when you expect to return.
            </li>
            <li> Whenever possible, avoid walking alone at night. Opt for well-lit and busy routes or consider using public transportation.
            </li>
        </ul>
